{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775890292159,"sessionID":"ses_284b12e61ffegKYv9ZTZvGCjkO","part":{"id":"prt_d7b4f57b7001CWy7JHgTDq8siW","messageID":"msg_d7b4f43e6001L43QSkk9tzClaQ","sessionID":"ses_284b12e61ffegKYv9ZTZvGCjkO","type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"toolu_4c949a803d574fb685c59fd3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"ls -la /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sdk-python/tests/","description":"List tests directory structure"},"output":"total 24\ndrwxr-xr-x 5 root root 4096 Apr 11 11:10 .\ndrwxr-xr-x 8 root root 4096 Apr 11 11:31 ..\n-rw-r--r-- 1 root root   42 Apr 11 11:07 __init__.py\ndrwxr-xr-x 3 root root 4096 Apr 11 11:13 integration\ndrwxr-xr-x 2 root root 4096 Apr 11 11:10 __pycache__\ndrwxr-xr-x 3 root root 4096 Apr 11 11:29 unit\n","metadata":{"output":"total 24\ndrwxr-xr-x 5 root root 4096 Apr 11 11:10 .\ndrwxr-xr-x 8 root root 4096 Apr 11 11:31 ..\n-rw-r--r-- 1 root root   42 Apr 11 11:07 __init__.py\ndrwxr-xr-x 3 root root 4096 Apr 11 11:13 integration\ndrwxr-xr-x 2 root root 4096 Apr 11 11:10 __pycache__\ndrwxr-xr-x 3 root root 4096 Apr 11 11:29 unit\n","exit":0,"description":"List tests directory structure","truncated":false},"title":"List tests directory structure","time":{"start":1775890292141,"end":1775890292158}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775890292167,"sessionID":"ses_284b12e61ffegKYv9ZTZvGCjkO","part":{"id":"prt_d7b4f52970014BXoFc5G2E5OfS","messageID":"msg_d7b4f43e6001L43QSkk9tzClaQ","sessionID":"ses_284b12e61ffegKYv9ZTZvGCjkO","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_eb9ccaaa523b4ad7a1e3e4e0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sdk-python/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sdk-python/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-028: SDK AgentRuntimeClient — Technical Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **Module:** `sdk-python`  \n6: **Language:** Python  \n7: **Size:** M  \n8: \n9: This document provides technical implementation details for the `AgentRuntimeClient` feature in the AgentCube Python SDK.\n10: \n11: ## Architecture\n12: \n13: ### Component Hierarchy\n14: \n15: ```\n16: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n17: │       AgentRuntimeClient                │\n18: │  (High-level Facade)                    │\n19: │  - agent_name                           │\n20: │  - namespace                            │\n21: │  - session_id (bootstrapped or given)   │\n22: │  - dp_client                            │\n23: └─────────────────────────────────────────┘\n24:                     │\n25:                     │ delegates to\n26:                     ▼\n27: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n28: │   AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient           │\n29: │  (HTTP Client for Router)               │\n30: │  - base_url                             │\n31: │  - session (requests.Session)           │\n32: │  - timeout / connect_timeout            │\n33: └─────────────────────────────────────────┘\n34: ```\n35: \n36: ### Design Patterns\n37: \n38: 1. **Facade Pattern**: `AgentRuntimeClient` provides simplified interface hiding data plane complexity\n39: 2. **Context Manager Protocol**: Supports `with` statement for automatic resource cleanup\n40: 3. **Environment Configuration**: Router URL resolves from argument → `ROUTER_URL` env var → error\n41: 4. **Session Bootstrap**: Auto-retrieves session ID from Router if not provided\n42: \n43: ## Data Structures\n44: \n45: ### `AgentRuntimeClient` Instance Attributes\n46: \n47: | Attribute | Type | Description | Default |\n48: |-----------|------|-------------|---------|\n49: | `agent_name` | `str` | Target agent runtime name | (required) |\n50: | `namespace` | `str` | Kubernetes namespace | `\"default\"` |\n51: | `router_url` | `str` | Router base URL | from `ROUTER_URL` env |\n52: | `verbose` | `bool` | Enable debug logging | `False` |\n53: | `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | Session identifier | bootstrapped or given |\n54: | `timeout` | `int` | Request timeout (seconds) | `120` |\n55: | `connect_timeout` | `float` | Connection timeout (seconds) | `5.0` |\n56: | `logger` | `logging.Logger` | Module logger | - |\n57: | `dp_client` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | Data plane client | - |\n58: \n59: ### `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` Instance Attributes\n60: \n61: | Attribute | Type | Description | Default |\n62: |-----------|------|-------------|---------|\n63: | `router_url` | `str` | Router base URL | (required) |\n64: | `namespace` | `str` | Kubernetes namespace | (required) |\n65: | `agent_name` | `str` | Agent runtime name | (required) |\n66: | `base_url` | `str` | Computed invocation URL | - |\n67: | `timeout` | `int` | Request timeout (seconds) | `120` |\n68: | `connect_timeout` | `float` | Connection timeout (seconds) | `5.0` |\n69: | `session` | `requests.Session` | HTTP session with pooling | - |\n70: | `logger` | `logging.Logger` | Module logger | - |\n71: \n72: ### Class Constants\n73: \n74: ```python\n75: class AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n76:     SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"  # Lowercase header name\n77: ```\n78: \n79: ## API Contracts\n80: \n81: ### AgentRuntimeClient Public Interface\n82: \n83: ```python\n84: class AgentRuntimeClient:\n85:     def __init__(\n86:         self,\n87:         agent_name: str,\n88:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n89:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n90:         verbose: bool = False,\n91:         session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n92:         timeout: int = 120,\n93:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n94:     ) -> None\n95: \n96:     def __enter__(self) -> \"AgentRuntimeClient\": ...\n97:     def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None: ...\n98:     def invoke(self, payload: Dict[str, Any], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> Any: ...\n99:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n100: ```\n101: \n102: ### AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient Public Interface\n103: \n104: ```python\n105: class AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n106:     SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n107: \n108:     def __init__(\n109:         self,\n110:         router_url: str,\n111:         namespace: str,\n112:         agent_name: str,\n113:         timeout: int = 120,\n114:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n115:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n116:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n117:     ) -> None\n118: \n119:     def bootstrap_session_id(self) -> str: ...\n120:     def invoke(\n121:         self,\n122:         session_id: str,\n123:         payload: Dict[str, Any],\n124:         timeout: Optional[float] = None,\n125:     ) -> requests.Response: ...\n126:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n127: ```\n128: \n129: ### HTTP Contracts\n130: \n131: #### Bootstrap Session (GET)\n132: \n133: | Property | Value |\n134: |----------|-------|\n135: | **Method** | `GET` |\n136: | **URL** | `{router_url}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/` |\n137: | **Headers** | (session defaults only) |\n138: | **Body** | (none) |\n139: | **Success Response** | 200 with header `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}` |\n140: | **Timeout** | `(connect_timeout, timeout)` |\n141: \n142: #### Invoke Agent (POST)\n143: \n144: | Property | Value |\n145: |----------|-------|\n146: | **Method** | `POST` |\n147: | **URL** | `{base_url}` (computed in init) |\n148: | **Headers** | `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`, `Content-Type: application/json` |\n149: | **Body** | JSON payload dict |\n150: | **Success Response** | 200 OK, response body parsed as JSON |\n151: | **Timeout** | `(connect_timeout, timeout)` or `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` |\n152: \n153: ### Base URL Computation\n154: \n155: ```python\n156: base_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\"\n157: self.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n158: ```\n159: \n160: ## Error Handling\n161: \n162: ### Exception Matrix\n163: \n164: | Error Condition | Exception Type | Message |\n165: |-----------------|----------------|---------|\n166: | Missing `router_url` and `ROUTER_URL` env var | `ValueError` | Contains \"router_url must be provided\" |\n167: | Bootstrap response lacks session header | `ValueError` | `\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\"` |\n168: | `invoke()` called without initialized session | `ValueError` | `\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\"` |\n169: | HTTP error (4xx/5xx) | `requests.HTTPError` | Raised by `response.raise_for_status()` |\n170: | Network error | `requests.RequestException` | Propagated to caller |\n171: \n172: ### Error Handling Flow\n173: \n174: ```\n175: AgentRuntimeClient.__init__\n176:     ├─ Router URL missing → raise ValueError\n177:     └─ session_id is None\n178:         └─ bootstrap_session_id()\n179:             ├─ GET request fails → raise requests.RequestException\n180:             └─ Missing header → raise ValueError\n181: \n182: AgentRuntimeClient.invoke\n183:     ├─ session_id is None → raise ValueError\n184:     └─ dp_client.invoke()\n185:         ├─ HTTP error → raise requests.HTTPError\n186:         └─ Network error → raise requests.RequestException\n187: ```\n188: \n189: ## Testing Strategy\n190: \n191: ### Unit Tests\n192: \n193: #### Test File: `tests/unit/test_agent_runtime.py`\n194: \n195: ```python\n196: import pytest\n197: from unittest.mock import Mock, patch, MagicMock\n198: from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n199: from agentcube.clients import AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n200: \n201: class TestAgentRuntimeClientInit:\n202:     def test_init_with_explicit_session_id(self):\n203:         \"\"\"GIVEN session_id is provided\n204:            WHEN client initializes\n205:            THEN bootstrap is NOT called\"\"\"\n206:         with patch.object(AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient, 'bootstrap_session_id') as mock_bootstrap:\n207:             client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n208:                 agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n209:                 router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n210:                 session_id=\"test-session-123\"\n211:             )\n212:             assert client.session_id == \"test-session-123\"\n213:             mock_bootstrap.assert_not_called()\n214: \n215:     def test_init_without_session_id_triggers_bootstrap(self):\n216:         \"\"\"GIVEN session_id is None\n217:            WHEN client initializes\n218:            THEN bootstrap IS called\"\"\"\n219:         with patch.object(AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient, 'bootstrap_session_id', \n220:                           return_value=\"bootstrapped-session\"):\n221:             client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n222:                 agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n223:                 router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n224:             )\n225:             assert client.session_id == \"bootstrapped-session\"\n226: \n227:     def test_router_url_from_env(self):\n228:         \"\"\"GIVEN router_url not provided but ROUTER_URL env var set\n229:            WHEN client initializes\n230:            THEN router_url from env\"\"\"\n231:         with patch('os.getenv', return_value=\"http://from-env:8080\"):\n232:             client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n233:                 agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n234:                 router_url=None\n235:             )\n236:             assert client.router_url == \"http://from-env:8080\"\n237: \n238:     def test_missing_router_url_raises(self):\n239:         \"\"\"GIVEN neither router_url nor ROUTER_URL env var\n240:            WHEN client initializes\n241:            THEN ValueError raised\"\"\"\n242:         with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"router_url must be provided\"):\n243:             with patch('os.getenv', return_value=None):\n244:                 AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"test-agent\")\n245: \n246:     def test_timeout_defaults(self):\n247:         \"\"\"GIVEN timeout/connect_timeout not specified\n248:            WHEN client initializes\n249:            THEN defaults applied\"\"\"\n250:         client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n251:             agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n252:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n253:         )\n254:         assert client.timeout == 120\n255:         assert client.connect_timeout == 5.0\n256: \n257:     def test_namespace_default(self):\n258:         \"\"\"GIVEN namespace not specified\n259:            WHEN client initializes\n260:            THEN defaults to 'default'\"\"\"\n261:         client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n262:             agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n263:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n264:         )\n265:         assert client.namespace == \"default\"\n266: \n267: \n268: class TestAgentRuntimeClientContextManager:\n269:     def test_context_manager_enter(self):\n270:         \"\"\"GIVEN with statement used\n271:            WHEN entering context\n272:            THEN returns self\"\"\"\n273:         client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n274:             agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n275:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n276:         )\n277:         with client as c:\n278:             assert c is client\n279: \n280:     def test_context_manager_exit_calls_close(self):\n281:         \"\"\"GIVEN context block exits\n282:            WHEN __exit__ called\n283:            THEN close() is called\"\"\"\n284:         client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n285:             agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n286:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n287:         )\n288:         client.close = Mock()\n289:         with client:\n290:             pass\n291:         client.close.assert_called_once()\n292: \n293:     def test_context_manager_exit_with_exception(self):\n294:         \"\"\"GIVEN context block raises exception\n295:            WHEN __exit__ called\n296:            THEN close() still called\"\"\"\n297:         client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n298:             agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n299:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n300:         )\n301:         client.close = Mock()\n302:         with pytest.raises(ValueError):\n303:             with client:\n304:                 raise ValueError(\"test error\")\n305:         client.close.assert_called_once()\n306: \n307: \n308: class TestAgentRuntimeClientInvoke:\n309:     def test_invoke_with_payload(self):\n310:         \"\"\"GIVEN session_id initialized\n311:            WHEN invoke called with payload\n312:            THEN dp_client.invoke called\"\"\"\n313:         client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n314:             agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n315:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n316:             session_id=\"test-session\"\n317:         )\n318:         client.dp_client.invoke = Mock(return_value=Mock(json=lambda: {\"result\": \"ok\"}))\n319:         result = client.invoke({\"message\": \"hello\"})\n320:         client.dp_client.invoke.assert_called_once_with(\n321:             session_id=\"test-session\",\n322:             payload={\"message\": \"hello\"},\n323:             timeout=None\n324:         )\n325:         assert result == {\"result\": \"ok\"}\n326: \n327:     def test_invoke_returns_parsed_json(self):\n328:         \"\"\"GIVEN dp_client.invoke returns response\n329:            WHEN invoke completes\n330:            THEN parsed JSON returned\"\"\"\n331:         client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n332:             agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n333:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n334:             session_id=\"test-session\"\n335:         )\n336:         mock_response = Mock()\n337:         mock_response.json.return_value = {\"status\": \"success\", \"data\": [1, 2, 3]}\n338:         client.dp_client.invoke = Mock(return_value=mock_response)\n339:         result = client.invoke({\"test\": \"payload\"})\n340:         assert result == {\"status\": \"success\", \"data\": [1, 2, 3]}\n341: \n342:     def test_invoke_without_session_raises(self):\n343:         \"\"\"GIVEN session_id is None\n344:            WHEN invoke called\n345:            THEN ValueError raised\"\"\"\n346:         client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n347:             agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n348:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n349:             session_id=None\n350:         )\n351:         with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\"):\n352:             client.invoke({\"message\": \"hello\"})\n353: \n354:     def test_invoke_with_timeout_override(self):\n355:         \"\"\"GIVEN invoke called with timeout=60\n356:            WHEN request sent\n357:            THEN timeout=60 passed to dp_client\"\"\"\n358:         client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n359:             agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n360:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n361:             session_id=\"test-session\"\n362:         )\n363:         client.dp_client.invoke = Mock(return_value=Mock(json=lambda: {}))\n364:         client.invoke({\"message\": \"hello\"}, timeout=60)\n365:         client.dp_client.invoke.assert_called_once_with(\n366:             session_id=\"test-session\",\n367:             payload={\"message\": \"hello\"},\n368:             timeout=60\n369:         )\n370: \n371: \n372: class TestAgentRuntimeClientClose:\n373:     def test_close_calls_dp_client_close(self):\n374:         \"\"\"GIVEN close() called\n375:            WHEN method executes\n376:            THEN dp_client.close() called\"\"\"\n377:         client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n378:             agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n379:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n380:         )\n381:         client.dp_client.close = Mock()\n382:         client.close()\n383:         client.dp_client.close.assert_called_once()\n384: \n385: \n386: class TestAgentRuntimeDataPlaneClientInit:\n387:     def test_base_url_computation(self):\n388:         \"\"\"GIVEN router_url, namespace, agent_name provided\n389:            WHEN client initializes\n390:            THEN base_url computed correctly\"\"\"\n391:         client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n392:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n393:             namespace=\"default\",\n394:             agent_name=\"test-agent\"\n395:         )\n396:         expected = \"http://router:8080/v1/namespaces/default/agent-runtimes/test-agent/invocations/\"\n397:         assert client.base_url == expected\n398: \n399:     def test_session_header_constant(self):\n400:         \"\"\"GIVEN class constant accessed\n401:            WHEN SESSION_HEADER read\n402:            THEN equals lowercase header name\"\"\"\n403:         assert AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.SESSION_HEADER == \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n404: \n405:     def test_timeout_defaults(self):\n406:         \"\"\"GIVEN timeout/connect_timeout not specified\n407:            WHEN client initializes\n408:            THEN defaults applied\"\"\"\n409:         client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n410:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n411:             namespace=\"default\",\n412:             agent_name=\"test-agent\"\n413:         )\n414:         assert client.timeout == 120\n415:         assert client.connect_timeout == 5.0\n416: \n417: \n418: class TestAgentRuntimeDataPlaneClientBootstrap:\n419:     def test_successful_bootstrap(self):\n420:         \"\"\"GIVEN Router responds with session header\n421:            WHEN bootstrap_session_id called\n422:            THEN header value returned\"\"\"\n423:         client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n424:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n425:             namespace=\"default\",\n426:             agent_name=\"test-agent\"\n427:         )\n428:         mock_response = Mock()\n429:         mock_response.headers = {\"x-agentcube-session-id\": \"bootstrapped-session-123\"}\n430:         client.session.get = Mock(return_value=mock_response)\n431:         \n432:         result = client.bootstrap_session_id()\n433:         assert result == \"bootstrapped-session-123\"\n434: \n435:     def test_missing_header_raises(self):\n436:         \"\"\"GIVEN Response lacks session header\n437:            WHEN bootstrap_session_id called\n438:            THEN ValueError raised\"\"\"\n439:         client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n440:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n441:             namespace=\"default\",\n442:             agent_name=\"test-agent\"\n443:         )\n444:         mock_response = Mock()\n445:         mock_response.headers = {}\n446:         client.session.get = Mock(return_value=mock_response)\n447:         \n448:         with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\"):\n449:             client.bootstrap_session_id()\n450: \n451:     def test_bootstrap_makes_get_request(self):\n452:         \"\"\"GIVEN bootstrap_session_id called\n453:            WHEN request sent\n454:            THEN GET to base_url with timeout tuple\"\"\"\n455:         client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n456:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n457:             namespace=\"default\",\n458:             agent_name=\"test-agent\"\n459:         )\n460:         mock_response = Mock()\n461:         mock_response.headers = {\"x-agentcube-session-id\": \"session-123\"}\n462:         client.session.get = Mock(return_value=mock_response)\n463:         \n464:         client.bootstrap_session_id()\n465:         client.session.get.assert_called_once_with(\n466:             client.base_url,\n467:             timeout=(client.connect_timeout, client.timeout)\n468:         )\n469: \n470: \n471: class TestAgentRuntimeDataPlaneClientInvoke:\n472:     def test_invoke_sends_post_request(self):\n473:         \"\"\"GIVEN invoke called with payload\n474:            WHEN request sent\n475:            THEN POST to base_url with JSON body\"\"\"\n476:         client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n477:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n478:             namespace=\"default\",\n479:             agent_name=\"test-agent\"\n480:         )\n481:         client.session_id = \"test-session\"\n482:         mock_response = Mock()\n483:         client.session.post = Mock(return_value=mock_response)\n484:         \n485:         payload = {\"message\": \"hello\", \"data\": [1, 2, 3]}\n486:         client.invoke(session_id=\"test-session\", payload=payload)\n487:         \n488:         client.session.post.assert_called_once()\n489:         call_args = client.session.post.call_args\n490:         assert call_args[0][0] == client.base_url\n491:         assert call_args[1]['json'] == payload\n492: \n493:     def test_invoke_sets_session_header(self):\n494:         \"\"\"GIVEN invoke called\n495:            WHEN headers constructed\n496:            THEN x-agentcube-session-id included\"\"\"\n497:         client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n498:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n499:             namespace=\"default\",\n500:             agent_name=\"test-agent\"\n501:         )\n502:         client.session_id = \"test-session\"\n503:         mock_response = Mock()\n504:         client.session.post = Mock(return_value=mock_response)\n505:         \n506:         client.invoke(session_id=\"test-session\", payload={\"test\": \"data\"})\n507:         \n508:         headers = client.session.post.call_args[1]['headers']\n509:         assert headers[\"x-agentcube-session-id\"] == \"test-session\"\n510: \n511:     def test_invoke_sets_content_type_header(self):\n512:         \"\"\"GIVEN invoke called\n513:            WHEN headers constructed\n514:            THEN Content-Type: application/json included\"\"\"\n515:         client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n516:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n517:             namespace=\"default\",\n518:             agent_name=\"test-agent\"\n519:         )\n520:         client.session_id = \"test-session\"\n521:         mock_response = Mock()\n522:         client.session.post = Mock(return_value=mock_response)\n523:         \n524:         client.invoke(session_id=\"test-session\", payload={\"test\": \"data\"})\n525:         \n526:         headers = client.session.post.call_args[1]['headers']\n527:         assert headers[\"Content-Type\"] == \"application/json\"\n528: \n529:     def test_invoke_timeout_default(self):\n530:         \"\"\"GIVEN invoke called without timeout\n531:            WHEN request sent\n532:            THEN timeout tuple with instance default used\"\"\"\n533:         client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n534:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n535:             namespace=\"default\",\n536:             agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n537:             timeout=120,\n538:             connect_timeout=5.0\n539:         )\n540:         client.session_id = \"test-session\"\n541:         mock_response = Mock()\n542:         client.session.post = Mock(return_value=mock_response)\n543:         \n544:         client.invoke(session_id=\"test-session\", payload={\"test\": \"data\"})\n545:         \n546:         timeout = client.session.post.call_args[1]['timeout']\n547:         assert timeout == (5.0, 120)\n548: \n549:     def test_invoke_timeout_override(self):\n550:         \"\"\"GIVEN invoke called with timeout=60\n551:            WHEN request sent\n552:            THEN timeout tuple uses override\"\"\"\n553:         client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n554:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n555:             namespace=\"default\",\n556:             agent_name=\"test-agent\"\n557:         )\n558:         client.session_id = \"test-session\"\n559:         mock_response = Mock()\n560:         client.session.post = Mock(return_value=mock_response)\n561:         \n562:         client.invoke(session_id=\"test-session\", payload={\"test\": \"data\"}, timeout=60)\n563:         \n564:         timeout = client.session.post.call_args[1]['timeout']\n565:         assert timeout == (client.connect_timeout, 60)\n566: \n567:     def test_invoke_returns_response(self):\n568:         \"\"\"GIVEN invoke completes successfully\n569:            WHEN response received\n570:            THEN requests.Response object returned\"\"\"\n571:         client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n572:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n573:             namespace=\"default\",\n574:             agent_name=\"test-agent\"\n575:         )\n576:         client.session_id = \"test-session\"\n577:         mock_response = Mock()\n578:         client.session.post = Mock(return_value=mock_response)\n579:         \n580:         result = client.invoke(session_id=\"test-session\", payload={\"test\": \"data\"})\n581:         \n582:         assert result is mock_response\n583: \n584: \n585: class TestAgentRuntimeDataPlaneClientClose:\n586:     def test_close_calls_session_close(self):\n587:         \"\"\"GIVEN close() called\n588:            WHEN method executes\n589:            THEN session.close() called\"\"\"\n590:         client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n591:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n592:             namespace=\"default\",\n593:             agent_name=\"test-agent\"\n594:         )\n595:         client.session.close = Mock()\n596:         client.close()\n597:         client.session.close.assert_called_once()\n598: ```\n599: \n600: ### Test Coverage Targets\n601: \n602: | Module | Target | Key Scenarios |\n603: |--------|--------|---------------|\n604: | `agent_runtime.py` | 90% | Bootstrap, invoke, context manager, error cases |\n605: | `agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | 95% | URL computation, bootstrap, invoke, session header |\n606: \n607: ### Integration Tests\n608: \n609: ```python\n610: @pytest.fixture\n611: def agent_runtime_client():\n612:     \"\"\"Integration test fixture for AgentRuntimeClient\"\"\"\n613:     client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n614:         agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n615:         router_url=os.getenv(\"TEST_ROUTER_URL\", \"http://localhost:8080\"),\n616:         namespace=\"test\"\n617:     )\n618:     yield client\n619:     client.close()\n620: \n621: def test_agent_invoke_integration(agent_runtime_client):\n622:     \"\"\"Test agent invocation against live Router\"\"\"\n623:     response = agent_runtime_client.invoke({\n624:         \"action\": \"test\",\n625:         \"payload\": {\"key\": \"value\"}\n626:     })\n627:     assert response is not None\n628: ```\n629: \n630: ## Module Exports\n631: \n632: ### `agentcube/__init__.py`\n633: \n634: ```python\n635: from .code_interpreter import CodeInterpreterClient\n636: from .agent_runtime import AgentRuntimeClient\n637: \n638: __all__ = [\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]\n639: ```\n640: \n641: ### `agentcube/clients/__init__.py`\n642: \n643: ```python\n644: from .control_plane import ControlPlaneClient\n645: from .code_interpreter_data_plane import CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n646: from .agent_runtime_data_plane import AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n647: \n648: __all__ = [\n649:     \"ControlPlaneClient\",\n650:     \"CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\",\n651:     \"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\",\n652: ]\n653: ```\n654: \n655: ## Implementation Checklist\n656: \n657: - [ ] Create `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` with `AgentRuntimeClient` class\n658: - [ ] Create `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` with `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` class\n659: - [ ] Update `agentcube/__init__.py` to export `AgentRuntimeClient`\n660: - [ ] Update `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` to export `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n661: - [ ] Implement router URL resolution (arg → `ROUTER_URL` env → error)\n662: - [ ] Implement session bootstrap via GET request\n663: - [ ] Implement payload invocation via POST with session header\n664: - [ ] Implement context manager protocol (`__enter__`, `__exit__`)\n665: - [ ] Implement timeout defaults (120s read / 5.0s connect)\n666: - [ ] Implement per-call timeout override\n667: - [ ] Use lowercase `x-agentcube-session-id` header consistently\n668: - [ ] Implement HTTP session with connection pooling (10/10)\n669: - [ ] Write unit tests for all scenarios\n670: - [ ] Verify code coverage >= 80%\n\n(End of file - total 670 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-028: SDK AgentRuntimeClient — Technical Design\n\n## Overview\n\n**Module:** `sdk-python`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n\nThis document provides technical implementation details for the `AgentRuntimeClient` feature in the AgentCube Python SDK.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Component Hierarchy\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│       AgentRuntimeClient                │\n│  (High-level Facade)                    │\n│  - agent_name                           │\n│  - namespace                            │","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sdk-python/design.md","time":{"start":1775890292137,"end":1775890292164}}}}
